data.description: Expanded ranch with loads of charm. Designed with emphasis on comfort and family gathering. Big spacious living room and kitchen. Huge deck in the fenced backyard provides inviting outdoor space. 12x20 shed, currently used as a woodshop, has a large 2nd story, storage area. Covered front porch big enough for the entire family. Inside you will find built in bookcases, built in desk and many wonderful touches. Anderson windows were installed awhile back. Roof is approx. 10 years old. Includes stove, refrigerator, microwave, washer, dryer, freezer in shed and all window treatments. Note: drawers and bookcases in master bedroom that are staying, are not attached to the wall and can be moved. Gutter guards have been installed to make life easier. Located across the street from The Hampton Park, Park. Seller is offering buyer a $2500 decorating credit at closing. If you have been looking for that right home, you may have found it.
